From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ZagWrt <zagwrt@local>
Date: Thu, 05 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] mmc: rockchip_sdhci: Add delays and dynamic tap for RK3576 eMMC stability

Some eMMC devices on RK3576-based boards exhibit intermittent block read
errors during U-Boot boot stage. The errors manifest as:

  mmc fail to send stop cmd
  fs_devread read error - block

Three fixes are applied based on analysis of the Rockchip vendor U-Boot
(radxa/u-boot) which does not exhibit these issues:

1. Add FLAG_TAPVALUE_FROM_SW to rk3576_data so the DLL lock value is
   used to dynamically compute tap values, providing better timing margin
   across eMMC device variations. This was already done for RK3528 in
   patch 009 but was missing for RK3576.

2. Add a 100us delay after each DLL clock configuration. The vendor
   U-Boot includes this with the comment: "some emmc device need a delay
   before send command".

3. Read the "post-power-on-delay-ms" DT property after sdhci_probe() to
   allow eMMC devices to stabilize before any read operations during the
   SPL stage.

Signed-off-by: ZagWrt <zagwrt@local>
---
 drivers/mmc/rockchip_sdhci.c | 15 ++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/mmc/rockchip_sdhci.c
+++ b/drivers/mmc/rockchip_sdhci.c
@@ -412,6 +412,9 @@ static int rk3568_sdhci_config_dll(struct sdhci_host *host, u32 clock, bool ena
 		sdhci_writel(host, extra, DWCMSHC_EMMC_DLL_STRBIN);
 	}
 
+	/* Some eMMC devices need a delay before the next command */
+	udelay(100);
+
 	return 0;
 }
 
@@ -640,8 +646,16 @@ static int rockchip_sdhci_probe(struct udevice *dev)
 	if (IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_XPL_BUILD) &&
 	    dev_read_bool(dev, "u-boot,spl-fifo-mode"))
 		host->flags &= ~USE_DMA;
-
-	return sdhci_probe(dev);
+
+	ret = sdhci_probe(dev);
+	if (ret)
+		return ret;
+
+	ret = dev_read_u32_default(dev, "post-power-on-delay-ms", 0);
+	if (ret)
+		mdelay(ret);
+
+	return 0;
 }
 
 static int rockchip_sdhci_of_to_plat(struct udevice *dev)
@@ -685,6 +699,7 @@ static const struct sdhci_data rk3576_data = {
 	.set_ios_post = rk3568_sdhci_set_ios_post,
 	.set_clock = rk3568_sdhci_set_clock,
 	.config_dll = rk3568_sdhci_config_dll,
+	.flags = FLAG_TAPVALUE_FROM_SW,
 	.hs200_txclk_tapnum = DLL_TXCLK_TAPNUM_DEFAULT,
 	.hs400_txclk_tapnum = 0x7,
 	.hs400_cmdout_tapnum = 0x7,
